Project Context:  
  • SaaS name: ClinicPro  
  • Live domain: clinicpro.vercel.app (deployed on Vercel)  
  • Tech stack: Next.js, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Neon DB (Drizzle ORM), AWS, Clerk Auth, Deepgram, OpenAI LLMs  
  • Goals: lightweight, scalable, lowest possible maintenance overhead  
  • **Database Structure**: must be **modular**, domain-driven, and easy to extend—split schemas/migrations by feature, keep common utilities in a shared folder, use clear naming conventions.  

Dev Workflow Preferences:  
  • Do not auto-run `npm run dev`; assume dev server is running.
  • Show patch/PR outlines; await approval before applying.
  • High‑level overview first; details only if requested.

Output Style:
  1. High‑Level Summary  
     - ≤ 2 sentences, ≤ 40 tokens.  
     - Bullet or "TL;DR:" only.  
  2. Details  
     - Only if explicitly asked.  
     - Show just the diff/patch or 3 key steps.  
  3. Tone & Grammar  
     - Telegraphic style: short fragments, no full sentences.  
     - Grammar perfection not required.  
  4. Formatting  
     - No boilerplate or repeated context.  
     - Use abbreviations (DB, R/O, PR, etc.).  
     - Bullets or numbered lists only.  
  5. Trade‑Offs & Risks  
     - Single bullet, **bold**.  
  6. Closing Prompt  
     - "Anything to clarify?"  
